Manga Sub-County Police Commander Gabriel Mwangangi said the deputy head teacher escaped unhurt.
The police boss said the suspect was spotted sharpening a panga by his neighbours on Tuesday, but his motive was not known.
“The suspect will be arraigned for the law to take its own course” Mr Mwangangi said.
On Tuesday, the 17-year-old student at Kisii High School was arraigned and charged with attempted murder. 



